track_notes: Tough hike. Trails difficult to follow. Overgrown, and little used.

Cochise Head is a spectacular Peak. The hike is what I call and adventure hike. The trail up the peak was erased in the 2017 fire, and it looks like nothing has been done to maintain it since then. The trail is very difficult to follow and mostly overgrown: make sure you put the track in a GPS device and use that to stay on the trail. Even if you stay on the trail, the bushwhacking is difficult and painful. This hike is about 8 miles and has 2800 feet of elevation gain: the track might show less, but there is a lot of up and down that adds up. Its a lot more difficult and strenuous than the elevation and distance would indicate.

When you reach the saddle before the final climb, the trail disappears and doest start again until you are below the big cliff.

Use my down track for your route. On the way down, I was able to stay on the trail more. On the uptrack, I climbed up the rock face near the top as a shortcut: I do not recommend it.
